Subject: Request for Secure Cross-Account S3 Data Copy (PROD → NON-PROD)

Dear Cloud Platform Team,

I hope you’re well.

We have a requirement to copy data from the PROD S3 bucket to the NON-PROD S3 bucket for non-production use. Since the PROD bucket is encrypted using AWS KMS (SSE-KMS), we would like this implemented following AWS security best practices and least-privilege principles.

Below are the requested steps and controls for implementation.

🔹 Objective

Securely copy data from:

Source: PROD S3 Bucket

Destination: NON-PROD S3 Bucket

Encryption: SSE-KMS enabled in PROD (and potentially in NON-PROD)

🔹 Required Implementation Steps
1️⃣ Cross-Account Access Model (Recommended Approach)

Please implement cross-account access using IAM Role assumption, rather than granting root-level permissions in bucket policies.

Create an IAM Role in the PROD account

Trust relationship should allow assumption from a specific NON-PROD IAM Role (not account root)

Use External ID if deemed appropriate for additional security

2️⃣ PROD Account Configuration

A. IAM Role in PROD

Grant permissions:

s3:ListBucket on source bucket

s3:GetObject on source bucket objects

B. PROD Bucket Policy

Allow access only to the specific NON-PROD IAM role

C. PROD KMS Key Policy (Critical)

Since the bucket uses SSE-KMS:

Grant the NON-PROD role:

kms:Decrypt

kms:DescribeKey

Without this, copy operations will fail with AccessDenied (kms:Decrypt).

3️⃣ NON-PROD Account Configuration

A. NON-PROD IAM Role

Allow:

sts:AssumeRole (to assume PROD role)

s3:PutObject on destination bucket

B. NON-PROD Bucket Policy

Allow write access only from the designated NON-PROD role

C. NON-PROD KMS Policy (If Encrypted)

If destination bucket uses KMS:

Allow:

kms:Encrypt

kms:GenerateDataKey

kms:DescribeKey

4️⃣ Data Transfer Method

Please confirm the most appropriate method based on volume and frequency:

One-time migration → aws s3 sync

Recurring sync → Scheduled job (Lambda / EventBridge)

Large-scale or ongoing → S3 Replication or AWS DataSync

Kindly advise based on bucket size and expected transfer pattern.

🔹 Security & Governance Considerations

Please ensure:

No wildcard (*) permissions

No root principal usage

Role-based least privilege

CloudTrail logging enabled for audit

Encryption maintained end-to-end

No public exposure of buckets

🔹 Clarifications Required

Please confirm:

Whether this will be a one-time or recurring requirement

Approximate data volume

Whether versioning is enabled on both buckets

Whether object ownership or ACL considerations apply

We would appreciate your guidance on the optimal architecture and confirmation once the configuration is complete.

Please let us know if any further information is required from our side.

